Freescale's Yocto Project BSP
=============================

To get the BSP you need to have `repo` installed and use it as:

Install the `repo` utility:

$: mkdir ~/bin
$: curl http://commondatastorage.googleapis.com/git-repo-downloads/repo  > ~/bin/repo
$: chmod a+x ~/bin/repo
$: PATH=${PATH}:~/bin

Download the BSP source:

$: PATH=${PATH}:~/bin
$: mkdir fsl-yocto-bsp
$: cd fsl-yocto-bsp
$: repo init -u https://source.codeaurora.org/external/qoriq/qoriq-yocto-sdk/fsl-yocto-repo -b jethro_freescale_qoriq_sdk_v2.0
$: repo sync
$: . ./fsl-setup-env -m p4080ds

